<span class="displaytext"><b>for immediate release <br/> contact:</b> kevin madden (857) 288-6390 <p><b>boston, ma –</b> today, governor (candidate full) released a letter sent to the united nations secretary-general ban ki-moon urging "the united nations to revoke any invitation to president ahmadinejad to address the general assembly." </p><p>in his letter, governor (candidate last) wrote: </p><p><em>"the iranian regime under president ahmadinejad has spoken openly about wiping israel off the map, has fueled hezbollah's terror campaign in the region and around the world, and defied the world community in its pursuit of nuclear weapons – capabilities that make these threats even more ominous. as general david petraeus testified last week, iran is also supporting shia militia extremists and violence that is taking the lives of american soldiers and undermining the iraqi government."</em> </p><p>governor (candidate last) believes that the iranian regime's record demands that the united nations "take a strong stand against iran's president ahmadinejad." failure to take such a stand would be a setback to efforts to address the dangerous and deadly actions taken by iran's leaders. if the united nations fails to act, governor (candidate last) wrote that "the united states must reconsider its level of support and funding for the united nations as we look to rebuild and revitalize effective international partnerships to meet 21st century threats." </p><p>today's letter builds on the comprehensive strategy to prevent a nuclear iran that governor (candidate last) laid out in january 2007 at the annual herzliya conference in israel. as part of this strategy, governor (candidate last) called for the diplomatic isolation of iran. he also encouraged public pension funds to strategically divest from any businesses associated with the iranian regime's dangerous activities. in september 2006, governor (candidate last) ordered state government agencies not to support the visit of former iranian president mohammed khatami to the boston area because of the iranian regime's dangerous actions. </p><p>to read governor (candidate last)'s letter to the u.n. secretary-general, please see: <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/img/pdf/un_letter.pdf">www.(candidate full).com/img/pdf/un_letter.pdf</a>. also, to read governor (candidate last)'s strategy to prevent a nuclear iran, please see: <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/news/speeches/herzliya_conference">http://www.(candidate full).com/news/speeches/herzliya_conference</a>.</p></span>



